

CLI Solution
To allocate a public IP address using the Azure CLI, use the following command:

az network public-ip create \
  --resource-group <your-resource-group> \
  --name datacenter-pip \
  --allocation-method Dynamic \
  --sku Basic

Console (Azure Portal) Solution
To create the Public IP in the Azure Portal, follow these steps:
Go to the Azure Portal: Open Azure Portal.
Navigate to Public IP Addresses:
In the left-hand navigation pane, search for "Public IP addresses" and click on it.
Click "+ Create" to create a new Public IP.
Configure the Public IP Address:
Subscription: Select the subscription.
Resource Group: Choose the existing resource group where you want to create the public IP.
Name: Enter datacenter-pip as the name of the public IP.
Region: Select the region where your resources are located (it should be the same region as the associated resource).
IP Version: Select IPv4.
IP Allocation: Choose Dynamic or Static based on your requirements.
SKU: Choose Basic unless you need the features of a Standard SKU.
Review and Create:
After reviewing the settings, click Review + Create.
Once validation passes, click Create to provision the public IP.

Verifying the Creation of the Public IP
To verify that the public IP address was successfully created, you can use the following CLI command:
az network public-ip show --resource-group <your-resource-group> --name datacenter-pip
